    The Soulmate Timeline

    Inspired by Novvafox’s Timeline Twenty-Eight, if Homura couldn’t get out of the thing immediately, though not a one for one match, as well as ‘A Bit of Luck and a Hospital Visit’ by Orajje that started to genesis while I was writing 'Kwami Magi Homura Magica' and I studied other Madoka fics for inspiration and a read on the fanbase at large.

    So I myself am known for my love and defense of harem slash multiship fics, and I will admit, seeing people’s reaction to Soulbond fics reminds me of reactions to those. Naturally they are (usually) distinct in their ship count, but they do seem to suffer from similar problems of how they are implemented. It just happens without... well thought about how it would actually function. World building issues, characters acting weirdly, and ships that don’t make sense.

    So hence why I thought it would be a bit fun to explore the concept with both characters from a Soulmate verse, and a character who is not from it and is going to react to it like a normal person. Add in the mess that is Madoka and let’s see what this one shot test looks like.

    A few notes.

    One: I feel like there are scenes I could do but didn’t, partially because it was getting longer than expected. If this was ever expanded on, I could probably fill them in. This is just me going ‘you know, I could explore Madoka’s parents more than I did’, because I write something that’s about 25K and can think of only the parts I skimped details on.

    Two: This would be expanded and continued only with the help of a Co-Writer. Otherwise this would stall out at some point. The idea is also adoptable by others completely independent of me, and in either scenario there are plenty of things I would consider or have no problem shifting up or changing as co-writer or as a reader of an adopted take. Honestly the one consistent thing to keep is that Homura enters a Soulbondverse of Madoka... with absolutely no idea what is going on and being contrasted with the native POVS. That is the one rule to keep.

    Anyway, let’s explore the idea my own way.

